    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cape Island</placeName>
                <date>1st July</date>.</p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I write this to say “how<lb/> do you do,” &amp; “good bye” I was
                quite<lb/> sorry I did not see you before our<lb/> departure. How did you enjoy<lb/>
                yourself ? Did you see many friends?<lb/> When you write tell me all about<lb/> your
                visit (I have forgotten the place<lb/> that you went to was it
                    <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> or <placeName>Salem</placeName>) The only
                news that I can<lb/> write about will concern all of our<lb/> family for I <hi
                    rend="underline">flatter</hi> myself that<lb/> you would be more interested
                in<lb/> our affairs that in strangers.<lb/> The weather has been delightful<lb/> so
                cool we bathe every day<lb/> expect the bathing will be a great<lb/> deal better
                next week on account<lb/> of the tide being higher (the tide is<lb/> regulated by
                the moon)</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The other morning <persName>Selina</persName> &amp; myself<lb/> were bathing were
                were not looking<lb/> at the breakers &amp; before we could<lb/> do anything down we
                went flat.<lb/> I was dreadfully frightened I<lb/> tried to
                    <sic>calck</sic><add>?</add> me but could<lb/> not at last a swell came
                &amp;<lb/> that brought me to the top<lb/> I swallowed a pint of<lb/> salt water.
                All my friends<lb/> tell me they think I am look<lb/>ing a great deal better when
                I<lb/> was here a day or two I weighed 86 &amp; this morning I weighed<lb/> 88—you
                can judge for your<lb/>self when we meet which I<lb/> hope will be soon you
                better<lb/> think of coming down it would<lb/> be a great benefit to you to<lb/>
                smell some fresh pure<lb/> salt air. I must now bid you<lb/> good bye as ma wants to
                write</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Ma &amp; <persName>Selina</persName> send their love to you<lb/> hoping to see you
                soon.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">I remain your fond</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Corinna</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. Kiss <persName>Dew Drop</persName> for me tell<lb/> her to <hi rend="underline"
                    >write me</hi> a letter.</p>
        </body>
